content.description: Same start as The Bludgeoning. After gaining the finger lock pocket move right to a sloper with a small catch. Get your feet high and stand up to the horizontal seam. Easy top out. Very different style from Bludgeoning even though there is only a difference of 2 or 3 moves.
content.location: NW corner of the Fishhead boulder. Shared start with The Bludgeoning, sitting matched on the diagonal incut.

content.description: Laydown matched in the jug hueco just left of the tree. Make two moves, get your feet up, and go for the lip. Top out is chill but might be worth brushing beforehand.
content.location: Just left of the tree growing out of the base of the boulder.

content.description: Start sitting matched on a diagonal incut that is just big enough for one and a half hands. Climb up to a finger-lock pocket and then crossover left to a small scoop on the high arete. Hold tension and go to the lip. A really fun problem on great stone.
content.location: North West corner of the boulder. Right hand side of the steepest section of the boulder. Shared start with Tuna Town on the diagonal incut.
